Project: Credit Card Customer Segmentation¶

AllLife Credit Card Customer Segmentation¶

Background: AllLife Bank wants to focus on its credit card customer base in the next financial year. They have been advised by their marketing research team, that the penetration in the market can be improved. Based on this input, the Marketing team proposes to run personalised campaigns to target new customers as well as upsell to existing customers. Another insight from the market research was that the customers perceive the support services of the bank poorly. Based on this, the Operations team wants to upgrade the service delivery model, to ensure that customers queries are resolved faster. Head of Marketing and Head of Delivery both decide to reach out to the Data Science team for help.

Objective: To identify different segments in the existing customer based on their spending patterns as well as past interaction with the bank.

Key Questions:

How many different segments of customers are there? How are these segments different from each other? What are your recommendations to the bank on how to better market to and service these customers?

Data Description: Data is of various customers of a bank with their credit limit, the total number of credit cards the customer has, and different channels through which customer has contacted the bank for any queries, different channels include visiting the bank, online and through a call.

  • Customer key - Identifier for the customer
  • Average Credit Limit - Average credit limit across all the credit cards
  • Total credit cards - Total number of credit cards
  • Total visits bank - Total number of bank visits
  • Total visits online - total number of online visits
  • Total calls made - Total number of calls made by the customer

subset_scaled_df=pd.DataFrame(subset_scaled,columns=subset.columns)
In [15]:
#running k means for different number of clusters.
clusters=range(1,9)
meanDistortions=[]

for k in clusters:
    model=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    model.fit(subset_scaled_df)
    prediction=model.predict(subset_scaled_df)
    distortion=sum(np.min(cdist(subset_scaled_df, model.cluster_centers_, 'euclidean'), axis=1)) / subset_scaled_df.shape[0]
                           
    meanDistortions.append(distortion)

    print('Number of Clusters:', k, '\tAverage Distortion:', distortion)

plt.plot(clusters, meanDistortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Average Distortion')
plt.title('Selecting k with the Elbow Method', fontsize=20)

Checking Silhoutte Score¶

In [16]:
sil_score = []
cluster_list = list(range(2,10))
for n_clusters in cluster_list:
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters)
    preds = clusterer.fit_predict((subset_scaled_df))
    #centers = clusterer.cluster_centers_
    score = silhouette_score(subset_scaled_df, preds)
    sil_score.append(score)
    print("For n_clusters = {}, silhouette score is {})".format(n_clusters, score))

Insights¶

There are three different groups of customer at the bank.

  • Cluster 0
    • Most customers in this have Avg Credit limit between 10k to 52k.
    • Most customers have 2 to 7 credit card.
    • Customers in the group visit bank more often than customers in other two clusters.
    • Fewer online visits were made by customer in this group.
    • Call made ranged from 0 to 4.
  • Cluster 1
    • Most customer in this group have limited credit available.
    • The total credit cards being used by these customers are fewer and range between 1 to 4.
    • Total Visits to bank were between 0 to 2.
    • Online visits range between 1 to 5.
    • Most number of calls were made by customers in this group, ranging from 1 to 10.

  • Cluster 2

    • Customers in this group have the highest Credit limit available.
    • Most customers have 5 - 10 credit cards.
    • Customers in this group made fewest visit to the bank.
    • Customers in this group use online banking more than others.
    • Fewest calls were made by customer in this group.

    ##### Business Recommendation

    • We can see customers from cluster 1, the ones with lowest avg credit limit seemed to have made the most number of calls. Bank can look into this and try to understand what services for this group of customer can be improved. Also, Bank team can target these customer with Marketing campaign to offer new services.
    • Customers in Cluster 1 are also the ones with lowest number of total credit cards. Bank can target this group to open new credit accounts based on their credit history.
    • Customers from Cluster 0 seemed to have visited the bank most, bank can investigate what type of services were seeked during the visit, attempt can be made to improve these services. Alternatively, bank can invest to develop online capabilities that could enable customer to complete those tasks online, there by increasing customer satisfaction.
